<div class="clear-simple"></div>
<h1 class="heading">Joe McCanta&rsquo;s never-fail hangover-relief shake</h1>
<h2 class="sub-heading padding-top-5 padding-bottom-15">This is the sommelier from Saf restaurant's sure-fire solution to overindulgence</h2>
<!-- END: Module - Main Heading -->
</div>
<div id="region-column1-layout2">
<div>
<div class="article-author">
<!-- Print Author name from By Line associated with the article -->
<span class="small"></span><span class="byline">
Chad Sarno
</span>
<div class="clear"></div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- BEGIN: Module - Main Article -->
<!-- Check the Article Type and display accordingly-->
<!-- Print Author image associated with the Author-->
<!-- Print the body of the article-->
<style type="text/css">
div#related-article-links p a, div#related-article-links p a:visited {
color:#06c;
}
</style>
<div id="related-article-links">
<!-- Pagination -->
<!--Display article with page breaks -->
<p>
The shake includes vitamin C-powered orange juice, raspberries and pineapple; 
cardamom and cinnamon, which help to cleanse the kidneys; stomach-soothing 
ginger; and banana, which acts as a natural antacid. 
</p>
<p>
<b>Serves 1</b>
</p>
<p>
- 50ml orange juice 
</p>
<p>
- 4 large chunks of pineapple 
</p>
<!--#include file="m63-article-related-attachements.html"-->
<!-- Call Wide Article Attachment Module -->
<!--TEMPLATE:call file="wideArticleAttachment.jsp" /-->
<p>
- 8 raspberries 
</p>
<p>
- 1 ripe banana 
</p>
<p>
- 1 thin slice of fresh ginger, peeled 
</p>
<p>
- 250ml soy milk 
</p>
<p>
- Pinch of cardamom 
</p>
<p>
- Pinch of salt 
</p>
<p>
- Pinch of cinnamon 
</p>
<p>
Blend all the ingredients in a food processor. Pour into a glass and drink. 
</p>
<div class="clear"></div>
</div>
<!-- End of pagination -->
